						<div class="postbody">This old thread is making me wish asm6 and ca65 would have a baby together. It'd be the best assembler ever.<br /><br />It looks like there are some funny edge cases ca65 has from being a one pass assembler, that a multi pass assembler can (apparently) easily resolve. Amusing that the author states they made ca65 a one pass assembler because it would be &quot;more fun.&quot; Haha. Yeah maybe, but also more annoying to use perhaps <img src="./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /></div>

